 was not for the utility of catching up to dragonfang, I disagree that more stuns and ways to disable people from controlling their character are good for rvr and this game.  I was using the example that while an infiltrator can easily obtain Envenom 50, doing an extra 80 damage per cycle, while a shadowblade or nightshade to keep their base damage on par could only do an extra 40 damage per cycle (via poisons - this number is largely based on where and how they specialize, of course.), I was curious how or if  you factored in that extra damage to the base damage - because frankly it does make a big difference.  As well as the enveneating poison line which reduces damage being done needs to factored in, since the infiltrator can reduce that by a greater margin than the other two (via poisons, again).<br><br>You have to factor in poisons to base damage, because they are always being used.  When one class can use a combination of higher poisons compared to the other two, technically it effects base damage.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ucyrionamon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyrion Amon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 9:59:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3657.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ashame this makes perfect sense...</span><hr size=1>    On ething, I don't know who ever started the whole thing about giving SBs a crush based weapon to spec ,but I'm against it.  As  Kobold SB, I'd much rather see us get a Thrust type weapon that could be at least partially based on my Primary stat as an SB.  I think that's a big one that's missing from you analysis of the 3 Assasins, 2 of them can spec a weapon that based off of their primary stat, one cannot.  I also think that the 2-hander option is much more of a liability than most will admit.  Unless you're going against greys, or siting targets you know that you can one-shot, the time-delay on a 2-hander is just not worth it, especially now that we all unstealth on a one-shot.  In addition to not being able to spec a weapon based on our primary stat, the one we can spec is Slash based, limiting our target selection severely.  At least if we had hte option of a Thrust spec, we can choose who we limit our targets to.  As it stands now, if an SB goes up against a chain wearer, he's suffering multiple negatives, some of which are forced on us.  You have the negative of slashing vs. chain, acceptable, since you chose the target, but we also have the negative of not speccing a weapon based off of a primary stat. (negative compared to the classes that can spec a Primary stat weapon)  We're forced by Mythic to use a weapon based off Strength, that's funny for a Kobold.  Even with Str buffs, I've never gotten my Strength up as high as my Dex, and I wear a lot of +str gear.  We need the option of a Thrust weapon to balance us out with the other Assassin classes.  <br><br>Jus tmy 2 coppers this Monday morning <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Gliling Ghostwalker<br>4x Shadowblade<br>Guinevere <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=biabia>Bia Bia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 10:07:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3657.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=to