l a line we spec in. Upping my base damage isn't going to do me any good IF they revamp the CS line (or any other line for that matter) and one day the 44th and 50th CS styles become more attractive. What then?<br><br>As a SB, even if respec was avaliable, I could not reach either style with a 5 spec template because of LA. At the moment, as things stand, I am a true jack-of-all-trades. I excel at nothing, but am quite decent at everything.<br><br>The other huge problem I'm having, is seeing both NS and Infs posting about &quot;Please don't allow SB's to spec thrust/crush etc.&quot; WHY THE HELL NOT?? Both NS and Infs get to CHOOSE what weapon they want to use. How is it not fair for SB's to want to be able to do the same thing? Especially kobold SB's who are forced into using a 100% STR based weapon. Soaking wet I might weigh 50 pounds and maybe even be able to bench press twice my weight...So tell me again why it isn't fair to give us a weapon we can spec in that takes advantage of our DEX?<br><br>~Drow<br>Kobold Shadowblade<br><br>&quot;33 pounds of twisted steel and sex appeal.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=biabia>Bia Bia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 5:21:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3657.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> /agree <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=3657.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=3657.topic&start=41&stop=53>3</a> </td>